<heading id="D0DB81E8FF8EFFEE1E98FB78E082F5EF" box="[174,737,1232,1260]" fontSize="36" level="2" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" reason="3">
<taxonomicName id="4C2C4D07FF8EFFEE1E98FB78E034F5EF" authority="Brown, 2003" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2003" box="[174,599,1232,1260]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Triphleba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schulmanae">
<emphasis id="B958EA96FF8EFFEE1E98FB78E3DFF5E8" bold="true" box="[174,444,1232,1259]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Triphleba schulmanae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B75FF8EFFEE1FF5FB79E034F5EF" author="Brown, B. V." box="[451,599,1233,1260]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" pagination="195 - 197" refId="ref3330" refString="Brown, B. V. A new species of Triphleba (Diptera: Phoridae) with bifurcate antennae from Baltic Amber // Studia dipterologica. - 2003. - 10, H. 1. - P. 195 - 197." type="journal article" year="2003">Brown, 2003</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13172A01FF8EFFEE1C50FB79E0C2F5EF" box="[614,673,1233,1260]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1685,1707]" captionTargetBox="[235,1186,494,1650]" captionTargetId="figure-10@2.[231,1190,488,1659]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Triphleba schulmanae: a — lateral view, b — dorsal view, c — anterodorsal view, with exposed bifurcate antennae; Prosphyracephala aff. succini: d — habitus, e — wings; Prosphyracephala kerneggeri: f — ventral, g — dorsal; Prosphyracephala succini: h — habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452494" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452494/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, a–c)
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B933684FF8EFFEE1ED5FB57E1E2F416" blockId="1.[227,897,1279,1301]" box="[227,897,1279,1301]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">
M a t e r i a l. SIZK K-27673, male, Klesov, 
<collectingRegion id="49E8F866FF8EFFEE1C4FFB57E0DAF416" box="[633,697,1279,1301]" country="Ukraine" name="Rivne" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">Rovno</collectingRegion>
amber, Late Eocene.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C336650FFF8EFFEE1ED5FA83E029F785" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B933684FF8EFFEE1ED5FA83E015F745" blockId="1.[174,1233,1323,1670]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">
A m e n d e d d e s c r i p t i o n. Body length 
<quantity id="4CD49B61FF8EFFEE1CE9FA83E113F445" box="[735,880,1323,1350]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" unit="mm" value="1.85" valueMax="1.9" valueMin="1.8">1.8–1.9 mm</quantity>
. Overall colour brown. Frons with seven pairs of bristles, lower SA minute, only 0.25 as long as upper SA. Antenna bifurcate, setose. Arista dorsal with sort pubescens. Palpus short, 
<quantity id="4CD49B61FF8EFFEE1D95FAC3E66FF485" box="[931,1036,1387,1414]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7999999999999998" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" unit="mm" value="0.18">0.18 mm</quantity>
, with 7–10 setae. Thorax with 1 
<emphasis id="B958EA96FF8EFFEE1F53FA23E317F4A6" box="[357,372,1419,1445]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">h</emphasis>
, 5 
<emphasis id="B958EA96FF8EFFEE1FA8FA23E3A0F4A6" box="[414,451,1419,1445]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">npl</emphasis>
, 1 
<emphasis id="B958EA96FF8EFFEE1FD8FA24E065F4A6" box="[494,518,1420,1445]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">sa</emphasis>
, 1 
<emphasis id="B958EA96FF8EFFEE1C06FA23E029F4A6" box="[560,586,1419,1445]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">dc</emphasis>
(short prescutellar pair); 2 pairs of strong scutellars. Tibial setation as follows: tb 
<subScript id="17A834C1FF8EFFEE1FC9FA16E064F4CF" attach="left" box="[511,519,1470,1484]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">1</subScript>
4–5 
<emphasis id="B958EA96FF8EFFEE1C73FA04E030F4C6" box="[581,595,1452,1477]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">a</emphasis>
or 
<emphasis id="B958EA96FF8EFFEE1CB6FA03E0FEF4C6" box="[640,669,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">ad</emphasis>
; tb 
<subScript id="17A834C1FF8EFFEE1CF3FA16E0AEF4CF" attach="left" box="[709,717,1470,1484]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">2</subScript>
1 
<emphasis id="B958EA96FF8EFFEE1CDBFA04E098F4C6" box="[749,763,1452,1477]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">a</emphasis>
in basal quarter, 2 
<emphasis id="B958EA96FF8EFFEE1DDEFA03E194F4C6" box="[1000,1015,1451,1477]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">d</emphasis>
in basal third; tb 
<subScript id="17A834C1FF8EFFEE1AFEFA16E6B3F4CF" attach="left" box="[1224,1232,1470,1484]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">3</subScript>
1 
<emphasis id="B958EA96FF8EFFEE1EF2FA64E2B1F4E6" box="[196,210,1484,1509]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">a</emphasis>
at end of basal third, 1 
<emphasis id="B958EA96FF8EFFEE1FC4FA63E06CF4E6" box="[498,527,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">ad</emphasis>
at midlength, 5(–6) 
<emphasis id="B958EA96FF8EFFEE1D31FA63E175F4E6" box="[775,790,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">d</emphasis>
in distal half. Wing length 
<quantity id="4CD49B61FF8EFFEE1A56FA63E6AFF4E5" box="[1120,1228,1483,1510]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.43" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" unit="mm" value="1.43">1.43 mm</quantity>
. Costal index 0.55. Costal ratios 3.3: 0.8: 1. Costal cilia 
<quantity id="4CD49B61FF8EFFEE1D66FA43E1DEF705" box="[848,957,1515,1542]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" unit="mm" value="0.04">0.04 mm</quantity>
. R 
<subScript id="17A834C1FF8EFFEE1DEAFA56E194F70F" attach="left" box="[988,1015,1534,1548]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">2+3</subScript>
fork elongate. All abdominal tergites fully developed, at most with short sparse hairs. Male genitalia with narrow epandrial process on each side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B933684FF8EFFEE1ED5F9E3E029F785" blockId="1.[174,1233,1323,1670]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">
<materialsCitation id="3B443CD9FF8EFFEE1ED5F9E3E026F785" collectionCode="R" pageId="1" pageNumber="246" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
<collectionCode id="ED3DAE41FF8EFFEE1ED5F9E3E296F765" box="[227,245,1611,1638]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">R</collectionCode>
e m a r k s. In the specimen on hand, the terminalia are somewhat concealed, as in the 
<typeStatus id="54978826FF8EFFEE1E98F9C3E37BF785" box="[174,280,1643,1670]" pageId="1" pageNumber="246">holotype</typeStatus>
, and cannot be examined
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
